s=1+1/n
\zeta(1+1/n)=n + a + b/n + \dots  =n + O(1)
\zeta(1+1/n)
\zeta(1+1/n)\lt 1+\int_1^\infty x^{-1-\frac{1}{n}}=1+n.
0\lt a\lt 1
\frac{1}{a}=\int_1^\infty x^{-1-a}\lt\zeta(1+a)\lt1+\int_1^\infty x^{-1-a}=1+\frac{1}{a}<\frac{2}{a}.
